The Houſe of John,
               Grot. in Acts 7.4 Surnamed Mark, being the place of our Saviour's eating the laſt Paſſover, and inſtituting his Holy Supper, the place where the Diſciples afterward aſſembled, and Chriſt came to them, and where the Holy Ghoſt deſcended;

this Houſes, I ſay, was afterwards, made a fair Fabrick, and a famours Church, as St. Hierom, and venerable Bede, both tells us.
